Metadata: Diterpenes from the brown alga "Dictyota divaricata" of the Indian Ocean

The brown algae of the family Dictyotaceae are a prolific source of diterpenes. The alga "Dictyota divaricata" has been subjected to relatively limited studies in which diterpenes of the dolastane type were reported from Caribbean collections. As reported here, a specimen of "D. divaricata" collected from the Andaman and Nicobar coasts in the Indian Ocean contains diterpenes of several structural types including five dolabellanes, six dolastanes, and a novel isodolastane diterpene. One of the dolabellanes has recently been reported from "D. paradalis" from the Great Barrier Reef.
